(299, '_transient_dash_88ae138922fe95674369b1cb3d215a2b', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://wordpress.org/news/2016/02/experiment-wordcamp-incubator/''>Experiment: WordCamp Incubator</a> <span class="rss-date">February 18, 2016</span><div class="rssSummary">WordCamps are locally-organized WordPress conferences that happen all over the world (and are so fun). Sometimes people don’t realize that WordCamps are organized by local volunteers rather than a central organization, and they contact us asking, “Can you bring WordCamp to my city?” When this happens, we always suggest they start with a meetup group, and think about [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://ma.tt/2016/02/jazzy-claire-de-lune/''>Matt: Jazzy Claire de Lune</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://poststatus.com/all-things-http2-and-https-draft-podcast/''>Post Status: All things HTTP/2 and HTTPS — Draft podcast</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/hack-summit-event-for-developers-will-be-live-streamed-february-22-24''>WPTavern: hack.summit() Event for Developers Will Be Live-Streamed February 22-24</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
